        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> January 5611</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">The kindly feeling always exhibited<lb/> by you towards me during my residence in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> emboldens me to request of you now the favor that<lb/> you will please acquaint me at the earliest possible opportunity<lb/> with the name of any established respectable congregation requiring the services<lb/> of a person to act as Hazan &#40;after the German Minhag&#41;<lb/> Shochet and Mohel in either or all capacities&#44; as I think<lb/> it more than probable I shall be leaving my present situation<lb/> in <date>May</date> next. I can procure the necessary testimonials<lb/> as to my fitness for such offices in addition to those already<lb/> in my possession. Should you not know at present any<lb/> Congregation requiring the services of such a person you<lb/> would confer a favor on me by inserting in the next number<lb/> of the Occident the enclosed advertisement to be continued<lb/> until countermanded. Of course the charges for the same<lb/> which I am told will not be high I will readily pay<lb/> upon your so requiring either to your agent here <persName>Mr J H<lb/> Joseph</persName> or to any other of your friends you may name.<lb/> Perhaps you would be kind enough to permit all<lb/> applications to be addressed to you&#44; as you have done with<lb/> other individuals. I must beg further to trespass on<lb/> your kindness and request you to favor me with a line<lb/> so soon as your numerous engagements<lb/> will permit</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>acquainting me with the probability of <del>your b</del> my success<lb/> and your willingness to add to the many favors I have<lb/> already received at your hand the one which I now<lb/> venture to ask of you.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Trusting the present may meet you dear Sir&#44; in<lb/> perfect health&#160;&#160;I have the honor to remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">Yours very respectfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">E. Mendels</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>371 Walnut Street</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Pa</placeName></p>
          
